ProMED
<promed@usa.healthnet.org>
[CCHF -- Congo-Crimean hemorrhagic fever -- is endemic in this
area on the Pakistan-Afghanistan border, but the short incubation
period for transmission to the hospital staff (only hours) argues
against that and more for an acute toxic event. Could they have
been exposed to the leak of an anesthetic gas or other product in
the operating theater? - Mod.JW]
